issue.title: python3.10 compatibility

repository.name: ivadomed
repository.description: Repository on the collaborative IVADO medical imaging project between the Mila and NeuroPoly labs.

issue.body:
<!-- Hi, and thank you for requesting a feature! Please take the time to first consider NeuroPoly's guidelines on issues (titles, descriptions, issue labels) before continuing:
https://www.neuro.polymtl.ca/software/contributing#opening_an_issue
-->

### Motivation for the feature
<!-- Is your feature request related to a problem? Please provide a clear and concise description of what the problem is. Ex. I'm always frustrated when [...]
-->

Python3.10 is standard now: Ubuntu 22.04 came out last month and uses it as its default. But ivadomed is only marked compatible up to 3.9, meaning it cannot be installed on Ubuntu 22.04, or anyone else using an up-to-date system.

This follows https://github.com/ivadomed/ivadomed/issues/770.

### Description of the feature
<!-- A clear and concise description of the feature you would like added, and any implementation details you've thought of.
-->

Change

https://github.com/ivadomed/ivadomed/blob/1da019b80be95d99905579dc66de15538141e487/setup.py#L35

to read

```
    python_requires='>=3.6,<3.11',
```

and fix anything this breaks.


### Additional context
<!-- Add any other context (references, screenshots...) about the feature request here.
-->

Due to https://github.com/neuropoly/computers/issues/338, `ivadomed` now has to hide inside of conda envs set up like `conda create -n my_env python==3.8` when we are using it internally on `romane.neuro.polymtl.ca` or `rosenberg.neuro.polymtl.ca` to do research. And come to think of it, this would affect SCT too, which we usually run on `joplin.neuro.polymtl.ca` -- except SCT bundles its own conda.

It would be nice to have the flexibility to install ivadomed with the faster `pip install --user` or `python -m venv` again.

repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
## Why this is important!
This would have prevented [**build from source issues**](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/issues/11656) for e.g. Windows and Linux

=============================================
Since with python, we now have onnxruntime 1.12 (nightly)

It will be great we have (if possible nightly) non python onnxruntime 1.12 to get C++ and C# API using the model.onnx generated by python notebooks that require python onnxruntime 1.12 (nightly)

- Inference_GPT2-OneStepSearch_OnnxRuntime_CPU.ipynb => **gpt2_one_step_search.onnx**
- Inference_GPT2_with_OnnxRuntime_on_CPU.ipynb => **gpt2.onnx**

This will allow the c++ and c# developers to continue the development without waiting for the schedule 
[ONNX Runtime 1.12](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/projects/9) Release: **mid July 2022**
